  "body": "Our predeploys are currently written with an extremely error prone pattern using the `SafeExecutionManagerWrapper`. An example can be found [here](https://github.com/ethereum-optimism/optimism/blob/35b99b07cf9f3e02496783c565b3f82f7fb55fef/packages/contracts/contracts/optimistic-ethereum/OVM/predeploys/OVM_DeployerWhitelist.sol#L78-L89):\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/ethereum-optimism/optimism/blob/35b99b07cf9f3e02496783c565b3f82f7fb55fef/packages/contracts/contracts/optimistic-ethereum/OVM/predeploys/OVM_DeployerWhitelist.sol#L78-L89\r\n\r\nThis (anti) pattern was particularly tricky when [implementing RLP transactions](https://github.com/ethereum-optimism/optimism/issues/496) because we need to compile REVERT and that proved difficult for the RLP contracts. This change is therefore blocking RLP.\r\n\r\n\r\n**Describe the solution you'd like**\r\nImplement `kall` which allows contracts to call low level execution manager functions when compiled with the normal OVM compiler.\r\n\r\nTODO:\r\n\r\n- [x] Update `solc` to include `kall` - https://github.com/ethereum-optimism/solidity/pull/22\r\n- [x] Update predeploys to use `kall` and test them in the `integration-tests` vs in the `contracts` package. - https://github.com/ethereum-optimism/optimism/pull/475",
